1
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:06,510
So how does this work?
I throw it like a real ball?

2
00:00:06,719 --> 00:00:08,755
Yeah, nice and easy, right over the plate.

3
00:00:08,959 --> 00:00:10,551
All right.

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:13,194
You suck, Wolowitz!

5
00:00:13,839 --> 00:00:14,908
What's that about?

6
00:00:15,119 --> 00:00:17,553
I'm heckling you.
It's a beloved part of baseball.

7
00:00:18,559 --> 00:00:20,709
He's right.
Given that you're probably still waiting...

8
00:00:20,879 --> 00:00:24,394
...to be picked for a game in fifth grade,
I'm sure you do suck.

9
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,951
-Hi. What's going on?
-Baseball.

10
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:31,118
Okay, this is not whatl meant
when I said go outside and play.

11
00:00:31,919 --> 00:00:33,830
-He's practicing.
-For what?

12
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:39,314
The Angels wanted an astronaut to throw
out the first pitch. So guess who they called?

13
00:00:39,519 --> 00:00:40,793
What? You? Really?

14
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:43,957
Well, a lot of people
who weren't available, but then me.

15
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:49,433
That's so cool. Congratulations. I guess
that makes you the athlete of the group.

16
00:00:49,639 --> 00:00:53,029
Well, notjust him.
May I remind you that you're talking...

17
00:00:53,199 --> 00:00:55,838
...to the seeker, beater, chaser
and water boy...

18
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,798
...of the third place Griffith Park Quidditch
team.

19
00:00:58,999 --> 00:01:01,991
Watching your boyfriend run around
with a broomstick between his legs...

20
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:03,752
...isn't something you forget.

21
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,873
-Come on. Now, throw one.
-All right, here we go.

22
00:01:08,399 --> 00:01:10,594
You look like ajackass!

23
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:15,351
-Cut it out. You're hurting my feelings.
-Now you know why we're not outside.

24
00:01:40,279 --> 00:01:42,031
Did you enjoy my lecture?

25
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:45,073
No, and neither did our waiter.

26
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,271
If you're going to serve
Cornish game hen...

27
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:52,069
...you should be familiar with the history
of Cornwall or be prepared to learn it.

28
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:54,753
It's hard to argue with that.

29
00:01:54,919 --> 00:01:59,435
And I know because I saw a sad man
with a pepper mill desperately try and fail.

30
00:02:04,519 --> 00:02:07,795
-Hey. How was dinner?
-Good, I had Cornish game hen.

31
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,116
Oh, that poor waiter.

32
00:02:11,719 --> 00:02:13,914
Sheldon, how about tomorrow
we see a movie?

33
00:02:14,079 --> 00:02:15,990
You guys are going out
two nights in a row?

34
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:19,356
I missed a number of date nights
while I was on my train trip.

35
00:02:19,559 --> 00:02:21,470
I'm contractually obligated
to make them up...

36
00:02:21,639 --> 00:02:23,789
...under the terms of the relationship
agreement.

37
00:02:24,559 --> 00:02:26,436
That's so hot.

38
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,834
It's better than hot, it's binding.

39
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:35,719
If you're free tomorrow night,
I'd love to have you join us on a double date.

40
00:02:36,079 --> 00:02:37,068
Aw.

41
00:02:37,359 --> 00:02:40,908
You are aware that a double date
doesn't count as two dates.

42
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,553
Oh.

43
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,151
Well, then come or don't. I don't care.

44
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,315
Can't believe you're sore.

45
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,796
Hey, even professional pitchers
need a rubdown after the game.

46
00:02:57,600 --> 00:03:01,718
They throw an actual ball.
You were throwing air at a TV.

47
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:07,155
For your information,
I also gave Leonard one hell of a high five.

48
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:11,430
I'm surprised you agreed to do this
in front of a stadium full of people.

49
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:15,189
Well, they're doing Space Day and NASA
asked me. I felt like I couldn't say no.

50
00:03:15,519 --> 00:03:19,751
Okay. If you want, I could help you practice.
I played a lot of softball growing up.

51
00:03:20,279 --> 00:03:21,917
Thank you, that would be great.

52
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:25,715
While we're at it, maybe we can butch up
your run for when you head to the mound.

53
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,997
What's wrong with the way I run?

54
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:31,034
Just kidding. Nothing.

55
00:03:39,559 --> 00:03:42,278
Sheldon, I'm surprised
you'd choose to go to a pub.

56
00:03:42,519 --> 00:03:46,228
At our committee meeting,
Amy made a motion for a picnic in a park...

57
00:03:46,439 --> 00:03:50,796
...but I tacked so many amendments
on that thing it sank like a lead balloon.

58
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,713
I then suggested a pub.

59
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:55,035
Yeah, which I was initially skeptical of...

60
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,998
...until I saw online that they serve
Yorkshire pudding.

61
00:03:58,480 --> 00:03:59,959
You don't like Yorkshire pudding.

62
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:05,553
No, it's yucky, but informing people about
the history of Yorkshire is yummy, yum, yum.

63
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:11,117
After a lively debate,
that proposal passed by a two-zero margin.

64
00:04:12,239 --> 00:04:15,390
Nice to see a busy couple
keep the spark of bureaucracy alive.

65
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,348
SHELDON:
Ignore them, Amy.

66
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:23,111
They're justjealous because they'll never
have a relationship as good as ours.

67
00:04:24,039 --> 00:04:27,315
PENNY: Isn't this when he says
"bazooka" or something?

68
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:29,038
SHELDON:
I wasn't making ajoke...

69
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,713
...l was merely stating facts.

70
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:34,508
Amy and l
have a superior relationship to yours.

71
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:37,280
You don't honestly think that, do you?

72
00:04:37,479 --> 00:04:40,357
Leonard, I assumed you knew.

73
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:44,234
The ranking of relationships
in our circle, by quality...

74
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,234
...is me and Amy, Howard and Bernadette,
Raj and his girlfriend...

75
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:51,591
...Penny and chardonnay, Penny and you.

76
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:55,277
LEONARD:
There isn't any ranking.

77
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:57,994
And if there were,
we wouldn't be at the bottom of it.

78
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:01,476
Yeah. And actually, I drink sauvignon blanc.

79
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:04,637
That's the part you have a problem with?

80
00:05:05,519 --> 00:05:06,554
Relax.

81
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:08,954
AMY:
There they go, fighting again.

82
00:05:09,359 --> 00:05:12,635
You'd never hear her
talk that way to sauvignon blanc.

83
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:19,196
So you never played baseball as a kid?
Not even Little League?

84
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:24,076
l was going to, but the day of tryouts
I found my dad's Playboy collection.

85
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,311
Threw my arm out.

86
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,470
All right, the pitcher's mound
in Major League Baseball...

87
00:05:31,679 --> 00:05:33,510
...is 60 feet, six inches
away from home plate.

88
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:38,350
Great. You take this and say when to stop.

89
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,312
-How much further?
-Keep going.

90
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:51,790
-How about now?
-l'll let you know.

91
00:05:54,119 --> 00:05:57,077
Are you saying "stop"
and we're just too far away to hear you?

92
00:05:57,879 --> 00:05:58,868
Okay, stop.

93
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,998
Are you kidding me?

94
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,354
That's 60 feet.

95
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,869
There's no way this is 60 feet.

96
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:11,035
I'm looking at it.

97
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,357
You realize this isn't one of those times...

98
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:16,589
...I want you to exaggerate
how long something is.

99
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:25,355
Okay, I gotta-- I just-- I gotta ask.

100
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:30,073
What makes you think your relationship
is so wonderful and ours isn't?

101
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:34,799
For starters,
we enjoy spending time together.

102
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:38,918
So do we.

103
00:06:39,119 --> 00:06:42,794
And I've seen you guys ignore each other
for hours doing totally different things.

104
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,197
It's called "parallel play."

105
00:06:46,599 --> 00:06:47,793
Yeah, toddlers do that.

106
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,309
Not as well as we do.

107
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,429
Can you believe this guy?
He has to be the best at everything.

108
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,511
So what? Why do you even care?

109
00:06:56,720 --> 00:07:01,111
Oh, listen to them.
Not even married and the honeymoon's over.

110
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:03,551
Whatever. You can't even go on a date...

111
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,676
...without checking your relationship
agreement.

112
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:09,195
If you've got a problem
basing a relationship on a contract...

113
00:07:09,399 --> 00:07:12,835
...l'd like to tell you about
13 plucky colonies that entered...

114
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:16,794
...a relationship agreement
called the U.S. Constitution.

115
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:21,637
And it may not be cool to say so, but I think
that love affair is still pretty hot today.

116
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,078
It's a good thing I'm not wearing
flag underwear right now...

117
00:07:27,239 --> 00:07:28,991
...because there's about to be a fire.

118
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,952
[MOUTHS]
What?

119
00:07:34,919 --> 00:07:38,070
Okay. It's not that hard.
You just look to where you wanna throw it...

120
00:07:38,239 --> 00:07:40,707
...step towards
where you wanna throw, and throw it.

121
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:48,033
That's your help? That's like saying,
"Here's how you fly a plane...

122
00:07:48,239 --> 00:07:52,630
...get in the airplane,
know where you wanna go, and fly it."

123
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:56,309
Just throw the ball.
Let's see what we're working with.

124
00:08:06,559 --> 00:08:07,833
Come on, Howard, fire it in.

125
00:08:32,199 --> 00:08:33,996
Throw the damn ball!

126
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,914
[POP MUSIC PLAYS OVER SPEAKERS]

127
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,832
So when do you guys
plan on getting married?

128
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,028
We're not sure.

129
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:46,636
But I want to wait long enough
to prove to my mother I'm not pregnant.

130
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:51,157
-Mayl have one of your fries?
-Of course.

131
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,873
Can I have a bite of your burger?

132
00:08:53,079 --> 00:08:54,876
Absolutely not.

133
00:08:56,279 --> 00:08:58,713
Some perfect couple.
He won't even share food with her.

134
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:02,550
It has avocado on it.
She's allergic to avocado.

135
00:09:03,199 --> 00:09:07,397
Are you so jealous of our relationship
you want Amy to die?

136
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,950
I'm notjealous.
I just think it's silly for you...

137
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:14,271
...to compare relationships
like they're something that can be quantified.

138
00:09:14,439 --> 00:09:16,111
Everything is quantifiable.

139
00:09:16,319 --> 00:09:18,753
That French fry? A seven.

140
00:09:18,959 --> 00:09:20,836
Spider-Man? A nine.

141
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:23,997
The number nine? Oddly, only a four.

142
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:27,996
-How ridiculous is he?
-A hundred.

143
00:09:30,359 --> 00:09:33,954
Sheldon, you're just assigning random
numbers to things based on your opinion.

144
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:39,028
No, I'm not. French fries have three variables:
crispiness, saltiness and shape.

145
00:09:39,239 --> 00:09:41,469
Which is why a curly fry only gets a two.

146
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:45,798
If I wanted curls for dinner
I'd order a clown wig.

147
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,713
Well, a relationship
is more complicated than a French fry.

148
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,912
Not according to the work
of Berscheid, Snyder and Omoto.

149
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:56,272
Oh, what did those rascals do now?

150
00:09:56,959 --> 00:09:59,348
They developed
the Relationship Closeness Inventory...

151
00:09:59,519 --> 00:10:01,987
...which predicts the stability
of a couple based on behavior.

152
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:07,279
Yeah, not to be confused with the French Fry
Goodness Inventory. That's pure Cooper.

153
00:10:08,199 --> 00:10:09,314
So this is accurate?

154
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:11,079
It's been around for 25 years...

155
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,874
...and has been extensively
corroborated by other researchers.

156
00:10:14,079 --> 00:10:16,274
Kind of takes the romance
out of relationships.

157
00:10:16,479 --> 00:10:18,993
Kind of? It does it perfectly.

158
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:22,553
Sheldon and I got an 8.2 out of 1D.

159
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:25,275
Fine. We'll take it right now.

160
00:10:25,479 --> 00:10:26,594
-No, don't.
-What?

161
00:10:26,759 --> 00:10:28,033
-Just don't take it.
-Why not?

162
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,276
It's stupid.
Who cares what number it is?

163
00:10:30,479 --> 00:10:32,515
-Come on, it'll be fun.
-I don't want you to.

164
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:34,948
I'm getting another drink.

165
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,913
Sorry.

166
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:45,237
I'm gonna let you count this as two dates.
They are a lot of work.

167
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,993
You think he's getting any better?

168
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,028
Yep.

169
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,193
HOWARD:
That was a close one.

170
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,352
Okay.

171
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,994
-Is it too late for him to cancel?
-I think so.

172
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:11,554
HOWARD:
Heads up. Watch out.

173
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:22,757
-Are you mad at me?
-No, stop being stupid.

174
00:11:23,879 --> 00:11:25,995
Um, phew.

175
00:11:28,119 --> 00:11:30,349
Is this about the test or is this about us?

176
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:33,677
I don't need a test to make me worry
about something I'm already worried about.

177
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,398
What are you worried about?

178
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:39,833
That we're engaged and have
nothing in common and it scares me.

179
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:41,273
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS OVER SPEAKERS]

180
00:11:41,439 --> 00:11:42,713
Yeah, that scares me too.

181
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:45,629
-It does?
-Sometimes.

182
00:11:45,839 --> 00:11:48,034
Well, that's not good.

183
00:11:49,599 --> 00:11:54,798
You being blindly infatuated with me was the
rock we were building this relationship on.

184
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,955
Okay, well, this might make you feel better.

185
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:02,079
Uh, we're both scared
that our marriage will be a disaster...

186
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:05,511
...and so that's something
that we have in common.

187
00:12:09,839 --> 00:12:12,797
Also, we both think I'm not funny. Heh-heh.

188
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,430
Huh? See, you're not laughing.

189
00:12:18,879 --> 00:12:20,870
[LINE RINGS]

190
00:12:21,079 --> 00:12:22,717
Hey, Froo! Loops, what's up?

191
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:30,109
Hey, Mike. Listen, NASA asked me to throw
out the first pitch at an Angels game.

192
00:12:30,319 --> 00:12:31,798
You got any advice?

193
00:12:31,999 --> 00:12:33,557
Yeah, don't do it.

194
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,713
What else you up to?

195
00:12:37,519 --> 00:12:38,838
Why shouldn't I do it?

196
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:40,074
There's no upside.

197
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,111
If you do well, no one cares.

198
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:46,308
And if you screw up,
you're an idiot on YouTube forever.

199
00:12:47,959 --> 00:12:51,588
But it's for a good cause.
What about all the kids that'll be there?

200
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:54,597
That's what I'm telling you.
Kids are the worst.

201
00:12:56,439 --> 00:12:59,511
My own daughter tweeted
[have a giant nose.

202
00:13:01,439 --> 00:13:03,270
Well, maybe I'll do a good job. Heh.

203
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:08,554
I don't know. In space you couldn't even
toss me a pen, and that was in zero gravity.

204
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,998
Okay, thanks for the pep talk.

205
00:13:12,199 --> 00:13:13,188
Anytime, Froot Loops.

206
00:13:14,319 --> 00:13:15,593
Give your wife a hug for me.

207
00:13:15,759 --> 00:13:18,831
She's so much cuter than you,
I don't know how you ever got her.

208
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:22,995
He's so nice.

209
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,712
Hey. Sorry about that.

210
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:33,273
No, we're sorry. We never should have been
comparing relationships in the first place.

211
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:35,629
Why? We won.

212
00:13:37,039 --> 00:13:39,269
I say next we take on
Koothrappali and his dog.

213
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,948
Really give ourselves a challenge.

214
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,633
I just want to say one more thing.

215
00:13:43,839 --> 00:13:47,912
Just because Penny and l are very different
people does not mean we're a bad couple.

216
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:50,714
The answer is one simple test away.

217
00:13:51,439 --> 00:13:54,556
You know, it's like when lthought
there was a possum in my closet.

218
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:56,591
Did I sit around wondering? No.

219
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,997
I sent Leonard in
with a pointy stick and a bag.

220
00:14:00,759 --> 00:14:03,557
I killed his Chewbacca slippers.

221
00:14:06,159 --> 00:14:08,434
-Let's just take the test.
-No, no, I don't want to.

222
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:11,153
-Because you know we're gonna do bad.
-It doesn't matter.

223
00:14:11,319 --> 00:14:14,117
I don't care if we're a 1D or a two.

224
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,635
Or a one. A one is possible.

225
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,677
Marriage is scary.

226
00:14:19,879 --> 00:14:23,667
You're scared, I'm scared.
But it doesn't make me not want to do it.

227
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:29,358
ltjust makes me want to hold your hand
and do it with you.

228
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,673
Leonard.

229
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:37,112
It would make me so happy
if you said things like that.

230
00:14:37,599 --> 00:14:40,591
We got an 8.2.
Trust me, you're happy.

231
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,074
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS OVER SPEAKERS]

232
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:52,717
Mm. I love how they put
a waterfall at center field.

233
00:14:52,879 --> 00:14:55,473
It really ties the whole stadium together.

234
00:14:55,639 --> 00:14:57,994
Look at you talking sports.

235
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:02,797
This is fun, huh? Get to see our friend
throw out the first pitch...

236
00:15:02,959 --> 00:15:04,392
...have a hot dog, watch the game.

237
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:05,879
Whoa.

238
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:08,156
Nobody said anything
about watching the game.

239
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,553
Sheldon, what did you expect?

240
00:15:12,319 --> 00:15:15,948
